## 5. Phase 0 criteria scoring for the C-extractor candidates

| Criterion | C-def-1 (finite-diff) | C-def-2 (multi-prec) | C-def-3 (op-tree) |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1. Computable | **pass** (float64 diff + div) | **partial** (mpmath sub OK; float128 limited) | **untested** (tree-walker not built) |
| 2. Survives M-subtraction | **N/A as filter — C is in the magnitude class but defined positively from inputs, not as a residue.** The Phase 0 §2 filter logic does not directly apply. The C-version of the filter is: "Is C a function of the route + fixture, distinct from a pure-M magnitude prediction?" Yes for all three. | (same) | (same) |
| 3. Discriminates (here = monotonic on rungs 1–4) | **pass expected** (it's κ-by-construction) | **pass expected** (precision slope tracks κ) | **pass expected** (algebraic aggregation IS κ) |
| 4. Named mechanism | **stated** (route's effective derivative) | **stated** (residue ~ C · 2^(-prec)) | **stated** (per-op condition number composition) |
| C-additional: monotonic on known-conditioning | **expected pass** on rungs 1–5; cancellation rung 3 is the discriminator from a pure-math-κ extractor | (same) | (same) |

All three pass criterion-level scoring at the design-scaffold level. **Empirical characterization (running them on the ladder) is the Phase 2 work product.**

